National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) in Nasarawa State says 1,900 prospective Corps members are expected to participate in the 2021 Batch ‘A’ Stream II Orientation course.  This is contained in a statement signed by Mrs Lucy Laha, Public Relations Officer (PRO) of the scheme in the state and made available to newsmen in Lafia on Monday. Laha said the  orientation course is scheduled to hold from May 18 to June 7, 2021 at the Magaji Dan Yamusa NYSC Permanent Orientation Camp in Keffi Local Government Area of the state. She added that the state’s Chief Judge, Justice Aisha Aliyu, is expected to swear in the Corps members on May 21, in a ceremony expected to be low key. She called on the public to assist the Corps members travelling from across the country to Nasarawa State to get to their destination without exploitation especially by transporters.